node.text: Here is a fun little window into our home practice with a 3 year old aka human jungle gym on a yoga mat. How cute is she powering through Sun A like a pro?!😍 Guruji @sofiephoenix will be running her own teacher trainings in no time. The end of the vid is pretty sweet too.. camping inside the yoga wheel has been her thang since she could crawl and she still fits in! Hope you’re keeping healthy and safe wherever you are in the world. After a whole month in lockdown, it’s finally starting to look like we could be returning to some kind of normal soon, so hang in there. Sending y’all virtual bear hugs from Down Under 🌏🙏🏽

node.text: As many of you know, New York is my first home. I’ve been speaking with my parents on the phone every day and I’m so grateful that they’re doing ok. Nobody in our family has been infected so far, but it’s breaking my heart to hear about the tragedy that is unfolding for so many others. We’ve been praying at the end of each day, sending our love and compassion to those in need. These next few weeks and months will be difficult in ways that are hard to fathom. If New Yorkers are in hiding, this virus has shown a knack for seeking. But, with time, this too shall pass and life will return to the city streets. The doors will open and we will meet again, greeting our friends face to face, at long-delayed Easter services and Passovers. Until then... stay strong, stay safe and look after each other. 🙏🏽

node.text:
If you’ve been binge watching your favourite shows or endlessly flicking through the 24hr news cycle, it’s time to hit that pause button and join me on the mat for a 15min asana sequence to open up the body and take your mind for a walk. Nothing fancy, just nuts and bolts instructions to some juicy slow beats. Btw I forgot the hip opener after lunge twist on the second side, so please add it in. At the end feel free to meditate for as long as you’d like and relax in savasana to finish your practice. Enjoy!

Fyi you can practice with us online on @alomoves with the first 2 weeks free when you sign up.

node.text: As all parents would agree by now, keeping your kids at home in self isolation makes them go stir crazy! These little monsters need to move, so how about some playtime with family acro!? Watch the second half to see us coach @sofiephoenix into RF2H (reverse foot to hand) in real time. To learn more, check out @acrovinyasa for tutorials on 180 earth & air asanas. PLEASE make sure you stay safe with a third person as a spotter, especially if you’re trying this for the first time. If you don’t have a spotter, a mountain of pillows should do the trick. Most importantly, always remember the golden rule of acro - if you’re having fun, you’re doing it right! We’d love to see you play so tag us in your videos. HAVE FUN! 😉

node.text: I often say that 8 hugs a day keeps the doctor away, but this time is different. As we all learn these strange new words like social distancing and self isolation, we’re quickly becoming touch deprived. Our hands are a direct connection to our heart. During early development around 6 weeks when the teeny heart beat is detectable, two flipper-like buds sprout from our heart and begin to grow into arms, hands and fingers just like tendrils of a flower unfurl from the stem to grow into lush, colorful petals. It’s profound to understand that our hands are a direct link to our heart, so when we touch others with compassionate intentions, we are literally experiencing a heart to heart connection. This self massage practice is a gift for YOU to send yourself some loving care. Enjoy!💛

node.title: POWER OF LOVING TOUCH 🙌🏽 Nurturing Self Massage

node.text:
You are not your thoughts. A pretty confronting statement, I know, but it’s true. In this video I share a simple practice of question enquiry called “mind the gap” which offers a glimpse into the simplest yet most profound truth about the nature of our mind. Btw I don’t know what went on with the audio in the vid, but it did add a pretty trippy vibe.

Ancient wisdom traditions tell us that we are infinitely greater than the innocent little thinker behind our eyes, and that we can all learn how to slip into the gap between our thoughts and intentionally shift into awake awareness - the phenomenon of Being. Different traditions have given it different names such as Truth, Grace, Emptiness, Silence, Peace, Source, Bliss, Being, Unity, Spirit, Enlightenment, but perhaps the simplest name is Awake Awareness. Although it is beyond description, living from awake awareness is a palpable experience and therefore learnable and teachable to anybody. The result is the discovery of a deeper sense of connection and purpose in every facet of your life.

If this resonates, check out the link in our bio to learn more about our 1:1 meditation course and mentorship. 🙏🏼

Do you remember Sigourney Weaver in Alien? That’s what we’re doing today!🤡 All jokes aside, if you’re feeling tension building in the cauldron of the belly from everything that’s going on right now, here is a soothing practice that helps in releasing it. Nauli and Agni Sara are ancient yogic cleansing practices (kriya or shatkarma) for vitality and optimal health, that massage the intestines and organs of the lower abdomen, effecting the entire digestive system. Regular practice also strengthens your abdominal wall and the surrounding core muscles. I know it looks weird, but it feels great once you get the hang of it. Give it a go and let me know how it feels. Happy to answer any questions in comments below.

PS pls excuse the crotch shot, just wanted to make sure you clearly see Nauli kriya in action. Also, I only did Uddiyana Bandha in the first practice, so for Agni Sara add a rhythmical pulsation of the abdominal wall in and out.

HOW TO:
This practice starts with Uddiyana lift which begins with a complete exhale followed by a hold and sucking up of the intestines and diaphragm into a vacuum created in the thoracic cavity. Stand with your knees bent, feet slightly wider than hip width, and the hands braced against the thighs. Lower the chin to nest in towards the collarbones, at the pit of the throat. Keep the stomach muscles soft and allow the abdomen to be drawn up, like an elevator, toward the chest. Try to maintain the internal lift and hold for several seconds.

For Agni Sara begin to rhythmically pulsate the abdominal wall in and out (didn’t shown it in the video). To practice Nauli, shift some of your weight over to one side and roll the rectus abdominus, which the long muscle that's often referred to as the "six-pack", or in this case a baguette along the back waist and toward that side. Continue to roll the abdominal organs in a wave like action along the inner rear surface of the abdominal wall. Complete one wave by rolling toward the front surface and back to where you began. Try each side several times.

node.text: Yes, there is a lot of fear in the world right now, but I’m here to remind you that as long as you have your breath, you know you’re ok. Here is my invitation to take a few moments out of your day to close your eyes and just breathe, to appreciate the fact that you are here, that you exist. The words “simply” and “effortlessly” are the subliminal themes of this mindful practice. So, find a comfortable seat, put on your headphones and tune in. Hope this helps in getting a bit of r&r in these turbulent times.🙏🏼

node.text:
We’re back in lockdown state of mind😕 Just as we thought we could all return back to some kind of normal, covid has other ideas. Poor/lucky baby Maya has had a very different start to her journey so far. To put it into perspective, Sofie had some 50+ flights and 11 countries behind her belt by the time she was 2yo. Not sure what effects that may have, but Maya is def a lot more chill!😸

It’s kinda hard to believe that after more than a year since the big lockdown ended here in Sydney, we’re back to square one. Now officially into a 3rd week of strict stay at home orders with infection rates on the rise and shortages of vaccines till September. A year and a half of closed borders and it looks like we still won’t be able to travel until sometime next year. 

Needless to say, we’re gutted to have to cancel our Bali teacher trainings and Nepal adventure retreat for a second year. BIG thank you to those of you asking us to simply hold your spots until the next time we can see each other. On the flip side, it’s been a great opportunity to practice letting go of expectations and simply surrendering to what is… you know, the real yoga😉 #silverlinings

THANK YOU for helping us open this exciting new chapter called @bodymindlifeonline 🙏🏼 We want to take a moment to send a massive gratitude blast to the entire BMLO team behind the scenes, who have been working crazy hours, pouring their heart and soul into bringing this innovative platform to life❤️‍🔥 @cgolfer @willcookyouanything @antheacesaro @inspire.play @haydensim @papapersuasion @socialetc Raewyn, Audrey, Aly, Craig, Melissa, Doris, Diego, our offshore dev team, co-founders @peteritippett & @philgood1001 and of course the entire @bodymindlife community!
